---
description: Use the code-context MCP tools (search, sql, reindex) for codebase questions — ranked local index instead of crawling files.
alwaysApply: true
---

This repository has a local code-context search index (MCP server
`code-context`). For any question about the codebase, prefer its tools over
reading files blindly:

- `search` — finding code, always: exact identifiers and error strings AND
  paraphrases / renamed symbols, one ranked pass. Hits include chunk
  content — answer from it directly when it's enough.
- `sql` — counts and rankings over the whole repo in one query, on
  `chunks(path, start_line, end_line, lang, content)`. Ranked aggregation:
  `SELECT path, SUM(end_line - start_line + 1) AS lines FROM
  bm25_search('chunks','content','<terms>', 300) GROUP BY path ORDER BY lines
  DESC LIMIT 15`. Regex via `regexp_like(content, 'pattern')` in WHERE.
- `reindex` — sync after significant edits.

Results cite path:start-end line ranges; open files only for what the
returned chunks don't show, and read just that range.
